{"id": "EUVD-2025-27915", "enisaUuid": "32f36384-7497-3ab2-aedd-f89231dda345", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nbpf, arm64: Fix fp initialization for exception boundary\n\nIn the ARM64 BPF JIT when prog->aux->exception_boundary is set for a BPF\nprogram, find_used_callee_regs() is not called because for a program\nacting as exception boundary, all callee saved registers are saved.\nfind_used_callee_regs() sets `ctx->fp_used = true;` when it sees FP\nbeing used in any of the instructions.\n\nFor programs acting as exception boundary, ctx->fp_used remains false\neven if frame pointer is used by the program and therefore, FP is not\nset-up for such programs in the prologue. This can cause the kernel to\ncrash due to a pagefault.\n\nFix it by setting ctx->fp_used = true for exception boundary programs as\nfp is always saved in such programs.", "datePublished": "2025-08-19T18:31:33", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-26T18:30:57", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0dbef493cae7d451f740558665893c000adb2321", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e23184725dbb72d5d02940222eee36dbba2aa422", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1ce30231e0a2c8c361ee5f8f7f265fc17130adce", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b114fcee766d5101eada1aca7bb5fd0a86c89b35", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-38586"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-38586"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "067111ec-1ead-3d3b-9502-ca8f05a25622", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.16.1"}, {"id": "19a2fbc9-b4a0-3028-937f-c508252c533d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.17"}, {"id": "1f4d4592-b083-3bca-8e1d-94a0875c4d4b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5d4fa9ec5643a5c75d3c1e6abf50fb9284caf1ff <1ce30231e0a2c8c361ee5f8f7f265fc17130adce"}, {"id": "3209f8f2-c7af-3c3e-8c5a-612f22942c67", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "6f6cbaaa-d9b9-35d9-affe-9a7fa81e1c81", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5d4fa9ec5643a5c75d3c1e6abf50fb9284caf1ff <b114fcee766d5101eada1aca7bb5fd0a86c89b35"}, {"id": "78a58df5-1536-34e0-a80d-786b8276f875", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5d4fa9ec5643a5c75d3c1e6abf50fb9284caf1ff <0dbef493cae7d451f740558665893c000adb2321"}, {"id": "93a069fe-1279-30fc-9be8-4afcdaf89430", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.17-rc1"}, {"id": "bfd4870b-9ebf-3375-b9d1-3b4de70f616f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5d4fa9ec5643a5c75d3c1e6abf50fb9284caf1ff <e23184725dbb72d5d02940222eee36dbba2aa422"}, {"id": "e07644e3-8744-3376-a31a-fe3ec331d6cf", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.15.10"}, {"id": "e4c5e3a2-5dc9-378c-b605-264f5ae0b38a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.12"}, {"id": "f7f1e033-6b8c-3b67-b135-da60a4a0056a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.42"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "8501e908-d624-3fc0-87d1-6f94e0947d67", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}